\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Mr Wildman was married in 1924 and born in 1900 at Oakworth, Keighley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 About - that would be Bridge - that would be when I lived at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Bridge Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} wouldn't it? Seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Number {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}five Mill Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember why the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 family}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  made this move from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bridge Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Mill Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well - I think it was for the convenience, there was - to avoid all these steps, attics and cellars and there was two bedrooms and a nice kitchen and - which there wasn't at the other one, we'd to go 
down in the cellar for everything. There was a nice living room and a nice kitchen and a nice garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bridge Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 it was all sort of on different floors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 It was all steps. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 There was only one room on each floor at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bridge Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. One room on each floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And I think you said your mother was rather a sort of nervous person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. And - I think she'd be - I think she'd been ill after my brother was born and the doctor thought she ought to get into 
more - where there was more company you know. It was rather isolated where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You said she found it a bit depressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. That's right, she found it depressing and miserable, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 It was a bit isolated was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well there's hou
ses below but we was really and just looking at a wall - a blank wall and some trees you know, and sort of a croft and - and it - the trees were very thick you know and it seemed to make the house dark. Anyway, I think that was the real reason she found i
t - the doctor suggested we went somewhere where it was more - more people about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And a bigger house as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. More convenient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 stayed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
 in the house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Mill Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 'Til I got married, yes. And they lived there 'til my mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well I think - I think I was the third child. I think there was a girl - I had a sister that lived about eighteen months and I think there were two stillborn children. But I was the first to live and the - I had a brother two years younger than I was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So there was just you and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Just two brothers, yes. My sister died. There was just me - me and me brother left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember what spacing there was between the ones that died and yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well I - I don't know much about them, I should I think - I really don't know but it couldn't have been so very long, couldn't have been, 'cos I think when I - when I was born I think my father was about tw
enty-six. I should - and I should think - I think they'd be about - he'd be about twenty-one or so when he - they were married, twenty-one or two. And so there must - it must have been within those two - those - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And the little girl lived to be eighteen months old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you know what she died from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
I rather think - I heard my mother say it was - what they used to call in those days consumption of the bowels. What would it be, enteritis or something. I can remember - I can rememb
er - they went to the mill you know and she put her out to be looked after when she was a baby. And she used to think that they gave her dope to sleep 'cos she was always sleepy when she came home. Anyway I think that what she died with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And they thought she'd been doped while she was being looked after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well, she - she thought - they always seemed to be dopey and sleepy at - when they came - when they fetched - they must have taken her in the morning and brought her back at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well I think he was twenty-six, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
I think originally he came from Bingley. And - moved about and me grandparents all lived at Bingley when I was, you know, quite grown up - Bin
gley and Morton they seem to moved about from me father's family. And I suppose they came to Oakworth to work at Haggas's, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When Haggas's opened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well think Hagga's be open before then but - I think they must have moved about from mills a bit in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was - comber really, and then he got - became an overlooker. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But he was a wool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 comber?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 He was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 wool comber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 , yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When did he become }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 overlooker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 , do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well as far as - as far - he was overlooker all the time I could remember really. I can just remember as a child when we lived at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bridge Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, he used to work over sometimes in the evening and I used to go down with his tea and a can, I used to go - take it - take y
our tea instead of coming home. And - used to take tea in a can and something - and give him some food. But - so I think then he was - used to see him in this combing place and washing the wool and that sort of thing. So I think pretty early on he must ha
ve become an overlooker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So you think by 1911 he would have been an overlooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes, he would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would he be overlooker in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 wool combing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  room?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. He went - there was the boss, you know, the manager. And then he was a sort o
f - I doubt whether he'd sort of ever served any time to - to overlooking you know but I expect nowadays you might call him the boss's assistant, you know, he didn't mind a machine or anything, he looked after the machines and - generally supervised under
 the boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So he'd look after a machine and see to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 other men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, would be the women - men and women - men and women yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So far as you know is that all he ever did, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 wool combing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  and then overlooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I don't think he - yes, that's all I - all my lifetime he worked in Haggas's mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You don't remember him doing anything before or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No. No, he never had anything after. And as far as I know he wasn't - he'd been doing it ever since he was a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did he ever do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well not 'til - he was getting on - after I was married. Used to short time, you know, the trade was bad. I can remember after we was ma
rried for a time there seemed to be - he was out of work then, but he didn't lose his job, they were more or less on short time if you understand, I don't think he was ever really out of - lost his job or anything but they were off for a week at a time yo
u know sometimes like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But before 1919 he was never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, never, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I think she was a bit older than my father, I think she'd perhaps be about - she may have been twenty-eight. I think so. As far as I know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you know where she came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well - they came from London, my grandmother used to - lived in London and me grandfather must have died when he was quite a young man and they had a - she had - they 
had - about four boys - four boys. about three girls. And the first - the oldest was married when the - and - and continued to live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And my grandfather died and - I don't know how it happened but she came - Haggas's brought them up here. They mus
t have - must have - you know, been seeking labour you see. Finding them a house and - got them a house. She came up with the - one son lived, stayed in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, 'cos he was already married. And one had already joined the Army. And so there was two other bo
ys and three girls, she came up to - to Oakworth. And I remember mother saying how - you know, how they got starting to - she'd be about nine, I think mother was about eight and how they were struck with the stone walls at they were getting up north you k
n
ow and the flinders. Yes, and - they got - they worked in the mill you see. Me mother went to mill - went to the church school and me grandma worked and the elder boys. If they were - they probably would enough to go because me mother wanted to go to work
 to mill and - she had to be - they had to go to see the doctor in the office and they did - if they'd got all their teeth they'd let them work. And she - I think she'd be about nine or ten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So if you hadn't got all your teeth you weren't allowed to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Look at their teeth, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2965629\charrsid13178822 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  said, if you'd got all your teeth you could let them work. That was - I suppose that was some sort of sign that you'd developed or something wasn't it. I think she'd be only - she wouldn't be very old, ten - perhaps ten 
or eleven. Yes, yes. Yes. She were ever so glad when they said she could start. She liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So she worked at Haggas's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What did she do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Drawing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Drawing in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 They call it - they call it roving and drawing, the d
rawing room. Me father used to like the combing and that's put onto big tubs and then it comes round and - and the drawing, they draw it off these tubs and they get into big bobbins, as big as that you know, right big ones. And then go from there to the s
pinning, you know, and they have to get less and less. 'Til it's - 'til it's - thread you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 This was after she was married, do you know what she did before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh she still worked - she worked there at Haggas's before she was mar
ried. Yes, from here being a girl. And she worked there, I suppose she worked there until - oh all her life she worked. And then I think after the - this experience with my sister when I was born they didn't put me out then. She managed - determined to ma
nage you know. And - apart from that she - she worked in Haggas's 'til I was born and then when I - when we were grown up, about eleven or so she went back again. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 
She worked at Haggas's and she worked at Haggas's - oh she was two or three years I think, and then after - I can remember - after - we started working she used to - do a days cleaning. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes, and washing for people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So once you started working she finished at Haggas's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I think she finished a bit before that but - it would be getting on for 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And then she just did the odd day a week cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
She used to have - she used to take washing in. For - just for one person. And then as I grew older she had a place where she went on the Monday and worked all day for half a crown
. Yes. It was quite - quite good in that day. I think used to wash for a shilling. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did she do that until she was quite old then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 She died - she went to that day's cleaning, I can remember her going out - oh right up to 1918 I should think. Yes. And after. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 It was just one a day a week she did cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Could yes tell me how many rooms there were in the house at 5 Mill Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 There was - two bedrooms, one large one and one a bit smaller. And
 a nice living room. And a nice big kitchen. Bright - bright and airy kitchen leading out to a garden at the back. And a cellar. Yes, a coal - just a coal cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No attic or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No - no, no attics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When you were living at Mill Lane did anyone else besides your parents and brother live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well just for a short time but it wasn't a necessity. There was a young man who was - connected - had been lodging with one of me father's relations, without father and mother. And - 
he - they had a big family and it - you know, things went wrong, and they - his - they turned him out so he came to our house late one night, turned; out, only a young man, because he'd stayed out too late you see so mother took him in. And for a time he 
l
ived with us. But it was you know for his benefit more than - wasn't that - wasn't that they wanted the money. And - and he lived with us - oh I can't remember - a few years. And then I remember as we were growing up my mother suggested to him, he had an 
aunt some - an old aunt and uncle lived on Mount Brew and she said, why don't you try - they were childless, she said, why don't you try see if they'd like you? And they were delighted. So he went there. And actually he was - he was drowned in the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 Dardanelles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 . Yes, so he never had much of a life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So he'd been turned out by his parents because he came in late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
They weren't his parents. His parents were both dead and it was his brother and his brother's - his brother and his brother's wife and thei
r family and she'd a lot of children and I suppose she was - plenty on with the family really and - like young boys do this. He had to be in by a certain time, he stayed out too late. Caused a bit of a rift in the family. Just for a time between them. But
 it blew over afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So he was a sort of lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, yes, he was yes. He worked at Haggas's as well, a dresser.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So you didn't have any other relatives or lodgers staying with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was all done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well I don't think so Mrs Cryer, I don't think - you know, she'd mend the - mend the clothes that wanted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 mending}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
 and all that sort of thing, kept everything in repair. But I never had any homemade clothes or anything like that I don't think, not from after being a baby, they do then don't they. But - after growing - after growing u
p she always managed us to have a new suit for Easter and a tailor made one at - Edwin - there used to be a tailors shop down in Oakworth and we used to have one for Easter Sunday. And then the - a new rig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 out and then that was for the Sunday best for the next year and the other one went for Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Then what happened after Saturday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I suppose it got round to weekdays then. Yes, if it hadn't already worn out. Yes, but we always - she always kept us nice you know. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember the shop where it was bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
The where we bought the suit? Edwin Feather. You know next - you know next door to the Post Office Mrs Cryer? That's it. It isn't a shop now but it was there. Yes, Edwin Feather. And his brother was the Post Office. Yes. Fea
ther the Post Office and Feather the tailor, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And you got them once every year at Easter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I think we used to have our new shoes - when we had the new suit we used to have new shoes and a new tie and - a
nd a cap you know. A right new }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 rig-out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
. I think we used to get them - well there used to be - sometimes - I think we mostly went to - we used to go to Gills where }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 Sunderland\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  is, you know that shops that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 closed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 , opposite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 Holden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  Hall there. Against the c
orner, that used to be a boot and shoe shop. Yes. And - and I think that - I can't remember going anywhere else for them. I think that must be it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And it was called Gills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Gills, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And the man there made the shoes did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Not all -
 no, he had - he was a shoe repairer but he didn't make 'em - the shoes to sell I don't think, they was manufactured. Yes, manufactured shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your father repair your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well he'd do such and he used to buy - boot protectors. Do you reme
mber them? They were bits of steel and used to put them on the heel and - and - on the heel and on the toe you know and sometimes on the side and it saved your soles. But we didn't - we had them proper soled and that, we took them to the - repairers. But 
