f course, all the - all weekdays we wore clogs and that meant - just - when your iron - be sure and tell your mother when your iron was off. 'Cos if you didn't get your iron put on straight away it wore the wood. So matter of going to the - used to be a -
 
opposite this Conservative Club there's a wood hut now with - that used to be a cloggers. I remember sitting there, we used to take your clog off and put you a new iron on, a penny for a front iron or an eel iron. So it's only shoes at - only shoes - your
 best shoes at Sunday and your second shoes for Saturday. Otherwise clogs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And your father would put these protectors on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, he'd do things like that, yes, to make them last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the ho
use such as cleaning and cooking, washing up, fires, decorating, repairs, improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No, I - I don't think he did many of those, no, he'd look after the coal and chop the wood and if they were washing at holiday time you know he'd hel
p with the washing. And I think he helped a bit in the Sunday dinner. But - I don't think - don't think he did any housework or anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember when you were small, do you remember him dressing you or undressing you or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well I don't remember him - I don't remember him ever - dressing or undressing us. But - was - was always kind to us and rocked us - rocked us an the rocking chair and sing - and singing all sorts of fashion songs to us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember him reading to you or telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes, he used to tell us stories. Yes, he was ever so good at telling stories, full of stories as well yes. But I don't think he did much reading. I remember him reading to me mother when she was ironing. S
he weren't much of a reader, well she couldn't - I don't think she was good at much at writing - she could write and read you know. When I was a little boy were doing her ironing and he was reading out of these Answers, you know, stories out of Answers, b
ooks like that you know. He also wrote the letters and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Had he stayed at school longer than your mother perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Probably. Probably would do because he's a bit younger you see, well - and - he may have stud - he may have gone to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes. Yes, he used to sometimes take us to Bingley, you know, he used to - he went to Bingley fairly frequently at Bingley Tide and - we used to go to - Boxing Day and various holidays. Yes, h
e used to take us to Bingley. And to Morton, to his brother's, yes, I've gone often, he use to take us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Just by himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, if my mother didn't want to go he'd take us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did he look after you if she went out, did she ever go out by herself and he'd take over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes I think so, I can remember - you know - especially at Sunday evenings if she went to church at Sunday evening he'd stop in with us, and - we didn't have - me mother didn't go out a great deal. But I - I'm sure he would have 
done if she'd wanted, if, you know, she wanted to go out. And he did do on occasion, specially - I can just particularly remember Sunday evenings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When you were young did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 
Well I don't think ever I had any really - when me mother was at mill and I was at school I used to have to come straight home and see the kettle was on boiling for - for when they come out of the mill - that was and for half past 
five and - I can - I sometimes used to, on a Friday - if I wanted to go to Oxford Hall to get a penny to go to Oxford Hall pictures, yes, on Friday I'd start and swill and do the windows at the back you know and -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You'd wash the windows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, wi
th a window brush, upstairs and down. Just see if she'd - - I could go to the pictures and have a penny yes. But I - apart from that there weren't any definite tasks I don't think, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your brother have any jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, no, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 These jobs such as putting the kettle on and swilling the windows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I did that for the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you do it after you left school or did you just do it for a short time?
