ll - cocoa and - I suppose we had - if me mother was - if we - on Sundays, a time when me mother was home we'd have an egg or toast. But I should imagine that when they were - when we'd had our breakfast ready we should be having treacle and bread and but
ter and - anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Something you could get yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, something you could get ourselves, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would your parents have something similar to that when they got home from the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes I think so. Yes, excepting the - you k
now, we had more at Sundays when they were at home than they had - eggs and bacon - perhaps bacon. But generally speaking I wasn't fond of it, bacon and fatty things, you know as a child I didn't like it. Not 'til I went into the Army.
