\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 If we had any worried? Yes I th
ink so, yes, we brought everything home. Me mother used to say that. If you're in any trouble bring it home, don't bring anybody else in, bring it home and sort it out. Yes, in the house, and don't - don't talk outside what we're - what we talk about in t
he house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 She didn't want you to repeat what went on at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes, yes, he was, yes. He was a jolly man, we used to come - yes, always telling funny tales and that sort o
f thing. Me brother took after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well he was a - a Yorkshire type you know, he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  that sort of - but he was - you know, very kind to us and - took - looked after us, yes, I think he - I think he was very affectionate towards us although they weren't demonstrative at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Not as much as your mother was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 If you had any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 worries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  could you have shared them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Yes, I think we were very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 communal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  you know, I think it'd be - wouldn't be apart, we should talk about it when all the family was in you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well I don't - I never remember - we used to be checked if we were cheeky or things like that but I don't think -
 I don't - I don't remember any specific rebellions or anything like that, we - they brought us up to be good mannered and - and respectful to people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brother in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I had to be ra
ther protective when he was a child because he was - the fact that he wasn't very strong, but he outgrew that and - but they didn't like us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 quarrelling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  or anything like that but to be - friends together, yes. And we always were I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, I don't remember them ever saying that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 
No, I don't think so, they used to - it was a general expression wasn't it, if you hit you, you hit him back.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 They never said this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, I don't think we had any troubles about that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well - I think, you know, me mother especially wanted us to grow up to better - in a bit better - in station. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3302408\charrsid13178822 They\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
 all - she - they - you know, they thought more about character, I don't think they particularly wanted us to be wealthy or anything like that but - wanted us to be somebody who looked - - people looked up to and respected. More that way. I don't rememb
er them telling you to get on or make money or anything like that. But she'd a high opinion of - people with good characters, you know, people in the village whom she respected and things like that, you want to grow up like so and so you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well religion I think. And - church, me mother - me mother more than me father. He - he was a - he - I think he'd been a Methodist but - she persuaded him to be confirmed you know. 
But he was - he was - he always backed her up, there was no argument against it, but she was a strong person even to being - when we were - in us twenties before I got married she was grieved if you missed church of Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What did they think of swearing, what would they say if they heard you swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh I don't - I don't think - they'd have been dumbfounded, yes, oh they would - they never used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You just never did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, they never did. And those were things that's - would have been pandemonium I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Mother used to say - not - you know, not in - say little - she'd say, little pigs have big ears. Or - she - no, not that, that's right, children should be seen and not heard, that's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would they allow you to talk if there were just the two of them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But if they had company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well - yes, we talked to them and that, we all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But if you talked too much they'd tell you to be quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes. They would, yes. I can't remember any incidents. Yes. We used to have quite a lot of company. Because my father's was a big family and in those days they visited didn't they. Went to the sister at Bradford and family from Morto
n, they'd come in on Sunday or - if it was a - if it was a stormy wet day and me mother used to say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  Sunday, it'll keep every}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  at home today. But often we had people in to see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Mother was very strict. I don't - there was - there used to be a strap hung up on the side of the - a little bracket and it was on there but it was there - it was there as a threat. I don't ever remember -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822  you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  know, ever remember having it used
 on me, but used to say, I'll get that strap to you if you - anything. It was there as a threat that. I can remember - I think me father would hit at side of head sometimes. But I never was thrashed or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Just a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Used to get smacked of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You don't remember your mother ever doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
She'd do - mother mainly really, she was the more - you know, she'd correct us more in order than me father did I think. But he would back her up you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 She'd give you a smack as well would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
She had more to do with us like and she would go on at us you know. Yes, but - she never did in the way - anything in the way of - of hitting us or anything I don think, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 She'd just carry on at you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. We stood a bit in awe of her like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What did she get very cross about, when she did get very cross and shout at you what sort of thing would it be about, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well - little bits of things, I can remember 
when she used to go to work. I used to take spoonfuls of cocoa and spoonfuls of sugar and mix it and eat it. And she could always tell, I always got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 found}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  out. And when they were at school I used to - when they were at mill in summer holidays - school holi
days I can remember routing in her drawers and making a tent outside you know. Used to get into trouble for things like that. You used - the last thing when she used to go she used to say to me, no routing up now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Can you remember any occasion when your father had to smack you and what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
I don't think so, only - if we were carrying on upstairs and if he got tired of shouting he'd come round hit us both at side of the head like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How did you feel when you were smacked, did you feel resentful or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I don't think so. No, I don't think so, no. It seemed - seemed to be usual order of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both our parents or did one play a more important part than the other?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well I think mostly me mother. But even to this day me father used to say, I always do it, this one thing, it's funny, I was - whenever there's an election, whether it' municipal, or whatever it is, I always go to vote because I always think me 
father always used to say, men fought for us to have this vote. So I - I always vote, so I always do even if I don't know who they are or anything. So he was on that side I'd take notice of him. But I think me mother - me mother was more keen about us man
ner of life and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Not a great deal, I can't remember, they used - I don't think - I don't think we used to get cards anything like that. I can't remember, no, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you get any presents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I don't even remember that. No. Might have got a penny or something you know, something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember having anything special to eat at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 At teatimes? Only at Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh a birthday you mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would your mother make a special tea or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You wouldn't have any little guests in, any friends in for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Oh yes, we were always all together. We used to go - we used to have our Christmas dinner together, all the four of us. And then we had an aunt - and an uncle and her sister and they hadn't any children and 
we went to their house for Christmas Day mostly, all the years - up 'til - 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You always went there for Christmas tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, we stayed - went to Battley - yes, for tea, and stayed 'til - into the morning you know, one o'clock or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No. Not 'til later - later years we had a piano but - not 'til after - that was - I was - that was about '23 I think. Oh excuse me, we had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 . Yes. Yes. I remember that. Played records you know, ten inches. It was about tenpence a record. Yes. But it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 otophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  they called it in those days didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was there anyone in the family who could sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I used to be able to sing, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 a choirboy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 , I used to sing solos, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you sing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes, me mother would - they would persuade me to sing when I was a little boy anyway. I used to have to stand by the jars and recite for the company or sing with us back to the - they were big jars weren't they do you remember how they
 used to be at fireplaces. Right big pillars you know. Used to stand by the jamb and recite or - for the company you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you ever sing altogether, make music as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
 at like Christmas when were at me aunt's you know and there'd be some more of the family there and we used to sing - sing Christmas hymns and things like - me father was one for singing. All sorts of local of local songs which I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you sing with him at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Sometimes, yes. But not - I don't think we sang much at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 It was mainly when you went out at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 We'd have a - together with the family. And there's most of the family would sing, me father would sing and some of me uncles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your parents play any games with you, either in the house or outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No, I don't think so, we used to play at - well - you know, card games, like - what did we used to call it - monkey or something. It isn't like - when we used to play whist and - me father - me father 
used to play patience, I can see him now at the table playing patience. And - I don't think me mother cared for it much, but snap and things like that you know, and we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 All four of you would play these games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. I doubt me mother would, she - she didn't play much. Perhaps me father and me and me brother and anybody else that was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you play dominoes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Used to play at - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 pat chaser}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  they used to call it, what would you call it, homeward bound or something, it was on a - on a board you know and dice and two - three coloured things and moved - and snakes and ladders and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You never had any games with them outside, like cricket or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh father was - I was - me father was in the
 local football club, used to be caretaker of the dressing room, looked after the dressing room and that sort of thing and I think he had a linesman sometimes, yes. I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But he never played any games with you outside?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 He never played, n
o, no. Not - not - you know, if we - perhaps if we had a cricket bat we'd play a bit in - outside you know with a ball when we were young you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were there any books in the house when you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I think so. I - remember me mother u
sed to have a book of - what would they call it, Girls Paper, and she'd had it bound you know, it was - I used to - I can remember from a child looking at the pictures in that. And then of course we used to get, every year, we used to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 prizes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  from the S
unday school, good books. And they were kept and carefully put away. We used to be able to take them out and read them but they weren't left lying about you know, had to look after them. I had them all 'til I was married. Yes. They've gone since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Your parents didn't have any books of their own did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
They used to have that - I can remember she had a - like a Charlotte Bronte which hadn't been out long of Mrs Gaskell. That hadn't been out long. And she had a book about Queen Victoria. It wasn't
 - I forget what it was called. I think it was printed at the Jubilee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You said she didn't read terribly well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No. She liked - she liked the Sunday Companion and books like that and they used to swap }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 with one another}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 . She used to take the Sunday
 - somebody used to give her Sunday Companion and she had - another book and me father were always taking books like Titbits or Answers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Magazines}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  these were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, they used to be about a penny you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you get the newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 We had an evening newspaper, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Britannica}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 . We used to get that, we didn't have a morning one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you get a Sunday newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes. Yes, used to have a Sunday newspaper, father did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You don't remember what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Sunday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Dispatch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  mostly I think it was, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And the Telegraph and Argus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 In the evening, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Can you remember your mother or father sitting down and reading in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I've seen - seen my father reading, yes. And I've seen me mother looking
 at a book, looking at her papers. Yes. But not much in - it's be a Sunday I should think. "think in an evening they'd be too busy if they'd been working, they'd have something to do at night. And she used to go out see some friends, and if she was - had 
any spare moment she'd slip up to see them or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Your father used to read aloud to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You don't remember your mother ever reading aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh no, I don't. No, never. I don't think she'd be that good reader you see.
 I know even when I was in the Army she never wrote, it were always me father wrote. He wrote all the letters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes - only my father and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You can't remember one before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Not - not in my - in our actual family you mean. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Your grandparents or uncles or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Oh yes. 1119. I don't think I do. I - if there was some child - you know, children of me aunts and that, I can remember me aunt - lived somewhere up ther
e she'd a lot of children and she had - I can remember those two - she had two funerals in six weeks. With children, yes. I had - either, heart failure or something like that, or smallpox or something. Two children - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 babies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  in six weeks. I remember them dy
ing and they had funerals. I think - well I remember going to see them. And I can remember me grandma's funeral. Me mother's mother. Being lifted up - in the - lifted up to look at her in the coffin, I remember that. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you actually go to the funeral of your grandma?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember what happened, who came?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Oh yes. I think she'd - she lived - like my aunt, they were - you know, here last marriage, she lived with her at last, you know, she wasn't married then. And s
he had - we had a - an uncle - she had a son and my uncle lived at Nelson and - she hadn't been so well and she went to Nelson and she had a seizure there and died there and then they brought her back to Oakworth. Well all the family was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you all go to the graveside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Went to the - went to the funeral and it was at - you know, and walked into the church. And - I remember we had a tea in the - mechanics after this, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did everyone wear black, mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I think so, they used to all wear black in these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Even you as a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
I'd only be - my brother was three when she died and I'd be about five. Well I suppose but I can't remember whether I - we was in black or not. I should think probably I would be, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you feel horrified or indifferent at being lifted up to see her in the coffin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No, I don't think so. But I can remember, and I've always said - said to me mum, she looks to be smiling. And - as we were all coming down fro
m the church, an older cousin lives at Bradford was crying. And I was amazed at him you know, and he says, we haven't any grandma now. I was a bit puzzled why should he cry, so it didn't seem to trouble me. No. I'd be about five I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were you taken out visiting relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Quite regularly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was it always your father or sometimes your mother who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Sometimes mother went as well, yes. Of course, we - they had relatives in Oakworth who we saw very - very frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Those were your mother's relatives were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Me mother's side, yes. Mother's side were mostly in Oakworth. And - then Bradford and there was frequent transits between Bradford and Oakworth, used to come on the workman and - me father - kept in t
ouch with all me father's - he's a big Family as well. Morton, Bingley, Steeton, all around.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What about your mother's brother who was left in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you keep in touch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. They had thirteen children and they all lived but one and - we've been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You'd visit them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes. Well I - not in - not in the younger days, I have done since I've grown older. But as far as I understand - she became up here frequently after me grandma came. I suppose - as each time th
ey're having children some of them came here, some of the children were sent up here while the mother was under confinement you see. And one of them stayed for years 'til she was a grown woman and - so they - and then me uncle, even in my childhood, alway
s came up every year, they used to go to the - they used to go in September so they could go to the Doncaster races. Yes. St Leger. And then afterwards, you know, when we came - came in contact, when we got older we used to visit them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So before 1919 you never actually went as far as London to visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh no, no, went no further than Blackpool I should think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were you taken shopping at the weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well we used to go to the Co-op, I can remember going to the Co-op with me fathe
r and that's Friday night, you had - you bought in for the week. We had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
 carpet bag and a big bag for potatoes. You bought flour and potatoes and everything for the week, I can remember that quite clearly. And - just occasionally me mother would go to
 Keighley on the Saturday. But not often. And then we - I'd go with her you know. We'd have - we'd go shopping bits of extras. We would go in a shop in the market, we used to get twopenn'orth of pie. Yes. But you'd to go right down to Oakworth station and
 then walk up, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Two penn'orth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  of pie, would that be meat pie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
They used - meat and potato pie, yes. You know, the - you know the usual ones what they used to make. And you'd get a plateful for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You'd eat it there you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, there in a - a sort of a restaurant in the market, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you eve go out with just your father, you used to go visiting relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. You see, well when we'd go - or pictures, when I used to work - when I was a boy at Co-op we ha
d Tuesday, everybody else had Saturday you know, there were never anybody at home at Tuesdays so I used to get me father to go with me to Oakworth pictures and we used to walk over. Used to come across - we lived in Mill Lane and we used to come across - 
across some fields there, somewhere where we lived, just over the wall and we'd be there in twenty minutes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 That was when you were about eleven or twelve was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, I'd be about - fifteen. Fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Now did it come that your father was not at work on a Tuesday afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh no, it was evening. Yes, evening, yes. Not in the afternoon - no. No, it'd be a Tuesday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, on Bank holidays for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 We used to go to Br
adford, that was a real treat. We used to go stop with - me mother's sister at Bradford. And they'd about - quite a nice family. Used to be - I remember them shoving us in - me uncle used to - they had two boys and me and my brother, and he used to put th
e
 bed up - you know, instead of being that way, he'd turn it round, make it that way with four little boys asleep all in one bed. They used to put us all in. And we used to go there and then we used to - go to Bingley at Bingley Tide and sometime - at Whit
suntide for the walks and that sort of thing. We had some relations there, and to Morton -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You never went to the seaside at Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well, not 'til I was - the first time I saw the sea was when I went - I was in the choir - the choirboys tre
at to Bridlington in 1910 I think. Yes. Then these - the same year these cousins at Bingley, their children, they took me to Blackpool - four days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So a Bank Holiday activity was usually to visit relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. We didn't go out much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Or go on a picnic or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You said you went with these cousins on holiday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you ever have a family holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, mother and father - the first - there's that first time I went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 
Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  in 19 - it'd be about 1911 I think. That was me father and mother, me and me brother and another couple and their - they had three girls and we all went together to }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 . The first time we'd all been to the seaside together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But you'd been for four days with your cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 That was by myself, I'd been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  for four days. But we all used to go together to Bradford to me aunt's and stop - you know, stop a day or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When all the family went you went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 , yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How long did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
A week. And Mrs Cryer, we had a big tin box like that, took all the bread for the week and the meat and everything, provisions, even your own bread you know 'cos I know it was getting mouldy towards the weekend. Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You just hired the actual accommodation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
We had - she cooked the meals and - and you know, did the bedrooms and meals, and cooked the meals for you and - but you provided all the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And you took it with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You couldn't have bought it there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
They called it apartments. Yes. Yes, well you could I suppose but - that was the general thing in those days, yes, yes. They always did yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 That was the first time you went in 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you start to go regularly then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No, I don't think so. 1912 - used to go - I used to go to me aunt's at Bradford - at school - for a fortnight. I was there - I was there that year when the war broke, you - know, when - that assassination in Serbi
a, in Austria, Serbia you know and I can remember I was there that week and - that were 1914 weren't it. I don't think we ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 went}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  away - away altogether again. The next time I went away was in - to the seaside, me uncle and aunt had a boarding house at B
lackpool, in Old Road, and I went with me aunt and an uncle who lived in Oakworth in 1918. But of course I was going to join up so they - me mother managed to save up you see and we had a week at Blackpool.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 This week you had with the family at Blackpool? Ye
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. At }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 
Well there was - there was me and me brother and then they had these three little girls, the others, and as far as I can tell most there was a - troupe called the Dandies and it was an outdo
or - pierrot show you know, under a shelter, some - there's a big picture place there now, I know where it was, and there was morning and afternoon and night, we went to all the sessions. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
You did - we sit - the children could sit in the front, you'd only t
o put something in the bag, you know, put a ha'penny or a penny. And I can remember we spent nearly all week there except apart from playing on the sands a bit. Yes. And they used to know where we were, the parents, and they just give us the money for the
 collection and off we'd go again, 'cos they used to vary the programme and when we came home used to have concerts you know, six of us, doing it all over again. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Before I left school? Oh I'll tell you, I can remember walking to Keighley as a boy, I used to walk to Keighley. And - go }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  the penny bazaar, I used to buy me mother penny ornaments and come back. Walk round the shops and walk back. And that was bef
ore the picture time. But afterwards we'd walk to Keighley or - if we'd been - if we'd been to Oakworth Friday night we'd walk to Keveney Street pictures. You know, not by myself, with some other boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But that was when you were a bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Be about - ten - no, be eleven, ten or eleven, yes, yes, ten and eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You could go out in the evenings then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. That was in the afternoon. Afternoon. Oh no we used to be home for the evening. 'Cos there used to be a lot of - a lot of activity 
on at the church school, concerts and tea parties and nearly always something on and we went to all these. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What would you do on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Sunday we got up, went to Sunday school at half past nine, church at half at ten. Went to Sunday scho
ol at two. And then when we got - when we got older we used to be in the choir again at six. Yes, the full day wasn't it. Yes, choir, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And you had special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes, Sunday clothes, yes, which }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 were put}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  - carefully bushed and
 put away. And all the house furnishings were carefully put away at Sunday night. Such as - brass fender, a beautiful brass fender and brass tongs and brass fire irons, which were never used, they were just there you know, for to - looked really lovely an
d
 - tidy up all round. And then they'd have special cushion covers and special table cloth. Yes, everything - that was - that was brought out Saturday dinner time you know. And then on Sunday night, I can see now, me mother used to be putting these away an
d - folded all up and putting the older things you now, putting the overalls over the band in front of the fire for morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was this because they took so much polishing she didn't have time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I think so, and - they took pride in their home, you k
now, decorated it up for holidays and that sort of thing. Oh yes, I think they - they used to be a day on Thursday polishing pan lids and brass - brasses and - and cutlery of course was always to be cleaned 'cos it was - it wasn't stainless steel then. Sp
oon polish and Brasso and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, I don't think we - I don't think we did really, no. We'd go for walks and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would you say that your parents thought it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well I certainly know that me aunt did, I can remember being at Bradford and there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 fire station}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 , a toy, and I was fearfully taken with it, but they wouldn't let me have it because it was Sunday I can remember. And I went to sleep in the 
afternoon and I thought it was Monday when I woke up. But still I couldn't have it because it was still Sunday, that's what makes me remember. But - I don't remember any particular restrictions at - 'cos we always had us books and - friends and that. And 
go for walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your parents attend church with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Me mother and father used to go in the evening. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And they both went to the Church of England did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 They went every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well, mostly, yes, generally, un
less there were visitors of course. If there were visitors came she couldn't go but we had to go - always went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were there ever any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Well just a minute, it was - there weren't any outings, it was - the walking day was the great day you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Was that at Whitsun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No, it was at - in July, there was the anniversary on the Sunday and they - walking day on the Saturday. A fortnight before the - before the parish - Keighley parish feast. And we used to - you know, 
have a band - a band - a - a band you know and we'd go to sing at the vicarage when it right - Bradshaw house you know, we'd walk right to Bradshaw House and then down to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Anson\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  where it used - where East Ride is now, that first house. Sometimes we'd go i
n the manor. And sometimes up to ; we'd go up this old lane and they used to open the gates for us so we could go to the doors, to go around Lane Ends then come back that way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So you'd walk all round the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 We
ll, we sang at - at the places. And the band played us round you know then we sang hymns at the various places where we stayed at. And then we had - we had a big tea in the school and all the children sat outside with school buns we used to call them. The
 right big - big spice buns you know, could have as many as you liked yes. Yes. Currant buns with - you know, plenty of fruit in. Didn't have any icing on, bit of sugar, you know, soft sugar, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You had that to finish off with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, that was - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 That was the end of the procession sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes, that's right. Yes. Then after that was a gala, there was a gala you know, dancing and - and sports. The - the gala'd be held in a field. Used to be opposite the club then. There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 
races}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  and prizes given and competitions and dancing for the elder people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Dancing in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 That's right, yes. Yes. Of course, excuse me, we always got choir trip, the boys were always taken to the seaside. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were there any other social activities organised by the church that you took part in, such as a concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Oh yes, I did, I took part in that. I was - been in singing and concerts and - I was good - I had a treble voice but I've never been able to sing since. But I had
 a good treble voice, I must have gad, they kept being in - in concerts and singing and then - in the choir. And this - the day school master at day school, his wife - she used to help me at concerts and used to be in those. They were a bit more classy li
ke. And - and there used to be tea parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What were the activities of the choir, what sort of outing did you go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well we went to - the first one I went to Bridlington. And I can remember everything about it to this day, when we got to Bridli
ngton I can remember where I sat. And then we went - I remember us going to Blackpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Would that be because it was your first trip to the sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 My first trip, the first time I'd seen the sea, yes. And - we - this choirmaster took us, I think we'
d be about fourteen boys, twelve or fourteen boys, and we had to be very early at the station, to get up very early, about six o'clock or something. And - we must have been so late back that - we missed - there was no train at the Valley, we'd to walk it,
 
so were - very late home and I went to bed and they were washing underneath in the kitchen, of course, there weren't underdrawing, you know, they could hear - and I slept through 'til three o'clock in the afternoon in spite of that. And then - we went to 
Southport and - Blackpool and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You always went by train did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 All by train, yes, there wasn't - there weren't much - no coaches was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You didn't have a wagonette or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, we had wagonette trips we used to h
ave in the Sunday school to Bolton Abbey - or to - up to Ades Hill for sixpence and we had gone in a coal cart there. Yes, they used to get man with a coal cart and then - or a wagon you know, put seats on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 This was with the Sunday school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes, and - you'd take your - your tea in a shoe box or something and then you'd - you could buy tea at the - there, you know where it is, right up by Collard Heath, and - I think we went there. Bolton - and to Bolton Abbey, yes. Used to have to get out 
and walk up the hills to save the horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And all the Sunday school went did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, yes. Certain classes you know. Perhaps a wagonette full.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did the church run any sort of temperance club at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Temperance club? No, they di
dn't, not here. They did at chapel I think because me uncle - I used to go to the Bank of Hope meeting at the Wesleyans. 'Cos me cousins went, they ere }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Wesleyans}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  and - and it was open was the Band of Hope and I used to go on a Saturday evening, they used t
o have, you know, lantern lectures and concerts and - and they gave prizes for attendance. I can remember getting a pocket knife once. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well if you went in the - say - the Church of England }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Men\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  Society and things like that I was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 You were a member of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 They never had a Boys }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Brigade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  or Scouts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes, I've been in the Scouts, yes. Yes, we had scouts, yes, I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So you were a member of the Scouts when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I can remember being in the Scouts when King Edward VII died and we all had to have a - a black - something in our scouts hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 It was something like a ribbon was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I think it was - a rosette or something, we had a - I know we had to have this black thing because he died in 1910 weren't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember what the activities of the Scouts were at that time, what you used to do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well I don't - I don't
 remember much about that. I can remember doing the - during the war we had - they were doing guards on the Pond End - you know, the water shelters some of them, I don't think I actually was doing that. And things like that and giving concerts for Belgian
 refugees and that. And going out and doing good deeds and all sort of things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When you were at home you had to say your own grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When the meal was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So your father didn't say grace before the meal started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
No. No, he wasn't - me father wasn't really a religious man. He was - you know, he didn't interfere with us but me mother was the religious one. And - and he went - I say - you know, he went because of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, we had to say our prayers. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember ever having family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, we never had family prayers. We used to, when we were young me mother had - before we went to bed she'd have us say 'em to her before 
- but afterwards, last thing we went upstairs, don't forget to say your prayers, you know, when we were - we scrambled them off sometimes and scrambled into bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, I think he did really. Was alway
s Conservative. I don't think he'd be - you know, I think he'd - I had another uncle that was Labour, in those days, or he would be Liberal or Radical then wouldn't he. And he used to cause some arguments. And - then we - I know they used to have some arg
uments like, me father should - was Conservative. I don't think he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Why do you think he held these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Oh I don't really, I don't know because - he was - he was of a - non-conformist background, all his family were non-conformist, you'd have 
thought he'd be more interested in Liberal, but he wasn't he always seemed to be - in the Tory because Tories were - he was Tory and that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well she - no, I don't think so, she - she used to take - you know, take i
t from me father I think. She used to think - she used to feel sorry for 'em - she'd think there are plenty of politicians.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember your father and mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I don't - 'cos me mother wouldn't have a vote would she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 In 1918 she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Yes, well if she did you see, I can't remember, she might have done. See 1918 I went in the Army and I should be away from home them. She probably would after that, me father always voted. Oh he made a - quite
 - you know, a point of it. About that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did he vote for the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh I think so, yes, I'm pretty sure he did. It was mostly Liberal and Conservative in those days wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 The Labour party was just beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 They just began, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if you father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No. No I don
't think so. I think Mr Arthur Haggas minded that - what did happen if you - if you left their works you know and did - and they wanted you - you could - you could - they didn't want you to leave the house. They'd want you to leave their house. 'Cos it wa
s
 all their property was Lane End. And of course there was their - there was no shortage - no shortage of labour always. And - I know families that left - sometime they'd be slack in the weaving and they'd go to another weaving shed around, as soon as they
 got busy they expect them to come back. Or if they didn't they'd be expected to move out of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So it was all right just going for a short period to another mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. When they didn't want - weren't needed. Some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 But they were expected to go back when they were needed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When they were wanted, yes. I don't think my father ever - and mother ever worked anywhere else. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 People have told me that they used to move between Haggas's and Attersleys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. And - another one
 yes, Attersleys, yes, that's right, or down there. You know, it used to be - I think particularly weaving - you know, had slack periods, yes, at the others, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember was your father a member of the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well he never 
- no, I don't think - remember - well I don't know if there was such a thing in them - he was a member of the Conservative club. And it was more - it was more a - it was a political club, now it isn't is it, it's like - more like a social club - a working
 men's club. But it was a Conservative club and he was always a member of that. Then there was the Liberal Club you know. The Liberal Club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember him working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, I don't - I don't think he did anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Do you remember your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, No, she wouldn't do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well me father would be up in his garden in summer. Or he'd be down in the cellar chopping wood, I can remember him, I'm just trying to think what he did. Or he'd gone to the club when he'd finished his jobs, he'd be out to the 
club. Me mother would be up at her friends, Coates's, or next door at Mrs Briggs, in the evening if she'd nothing on. She'd sit - she'didn't sit and read you know or that. If there was nobody in she'd say, happen say, I'll go up in Cates's a bit. And she'
d stay 'til - then come home and make us supper. But plenty of friends up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your mother have any interests outside the home, other than she had friends to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Well I think, apart from the church, I don't think so, no. She'd plent
y of them she knew at the works you know but - and I know like they always asked her - 'cos this is partly because - with the lady she used to work for - they used to always be a nurses ball they called it on Boxing day. For the district nurse you know, t
h
ey used to get the funds there, and they always asked her to look after the ladies cloakroom there. She always did that, that's about all I can - then of course it's - and at school at she used to work - serve at tea parties and things like that, washing 
up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 This }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 nurse\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  ball, it was to create funds with which to pay a district nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well there used to be a district nurse - well there used - that was it, and then they used - somebody else come round, you pay a shilling. Yes, and you had - you had a book, a shilling or two shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 And once you'd paid a shilling you could call on the district nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes, that's right. She used to live in Oakworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Well I don't ; she - oh perhaps she lik
ed going to see her friends you know, bit talk and gossip. And she'd go to a concert at school and anything - anything like and the dances like that she'd be in the refreshments washing up and doing - doing things like that. But she never - weren't one fo
r going to the pictures or anything like that much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When did you father get home from work in the evenings, what time would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 From work? Half past five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How many evenings a week would be spent at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 I don't think - I think
, it was pretty general to say me father, if he had any jobs to do, such as chopping wood, he'd do them or anything like that and go - then he'd be up to his garden and then he'd be on to the club. Yes. And they all came home at - well about nine or so or
 ten when we were at home and then my aunt, her husband's brother kept the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 Foresters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
 and he used to go up there and she'd be down at our house and he used to come - another cousin lived at Bridge Street and she'd be down at our house, my aunt, and then me U
ncle John called Aunt Pris and Percy called for Florrie and they went - by the - by the time they all come in it was quite an houseful before bedtime.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 So most nights most of the night would be spent at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Yes. Yes, I was the one that was at home mostly. When me mother was at home, together in the evenings, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Your father attended the Conservative Club, was it licensed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 How often would he go to it, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Oh I should think he'd call in most eveni
ngs. Not Sundays and not - I don't think not on Saturdays but - next week - most evenings he could have gone for an our happen. Play billiards or - they'd a billiard table you know and - reading room and things like that.
