Mainly in the street, yes. And then in the summer we used to play at - various seasons wouldn't there. There was - about Shrove Tuesday time you all - everybody had a whip and top. You had whips and top - and then later on another, marbles - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 tops}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  and marbles used to go. And girls used to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 battledores}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  and shuttlecocks and - checks, like square pieces of pot and bouncing ball and play - a game of chec
ks. And it was - you know, it was a right - I don't know what they - you know, they said so many words and so many bouncing and pick one up and put one down and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you ever play in the yard or in a garden or in other homes or in a field or anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 
Well we'd go in friends homes you know if it was - if we were invited, yes, but - it was bad weather going to that. But then look - chiefly looking at books or anything like that. Quieter wouldn't it. Yes, and you know we pla
yed hide and seek, you know, somebody'd hide and then go running round and - kick can and all sorts like that. Somebody'd kick the can and you'd to run and fetch it and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did you ever play cricket or football or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No, I never did much, no, my brother did but I never - never in - went in for them sort of games.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 When you were younger were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 At home? Ay. Yes. I don't think we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8079967\charrsid13178822 were ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822  told not to play with anybody. No. No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738450 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children in the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167447 GW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid818746\charrsid13178822 No. They were all - there were a lot of children down Mill Lane and we all sort of mixed in, I don't remember any restrictions or - you 
